                        ue the whole
house of our Land. Couetise would be charitable,
but there is that other summe to make vp.
Pride would giue, or at least forbeare to extort,
but there is a ruffe of the new fashion to bee
bought.* Dignity, a caroch, or strange apparell
is to be purchas'd; and who but the poore tenants
must pay for it! vpon whom they (once so
accoutred) afterward looke betwixt scorne and
anger: and goe as if they were shut vp in wainscote.
                     
