sends vs a plentiful raine. One showre will
not make vs fruitful; it must come oft vpon
us. Gutta cauat lapidem, non vi, sed saepe cadendo.
The raine dints the hard stone, not by violence,
but by oft-falling droppes. Line must be added
to line: here a little and there a little. God could
powre a whole floud on vs at once: but mans
vnderstanding

                              Is like a viall, narrow at the toppe:
