But good herbes giue a double sauour: one
outward to man, another inward to God. The
sweete smoke of a holy sacrifice, like a subtil ayre,
riseth vp to heauen; and is with God before man
sees or smels it. It also cheares the hearts of Christians,
to behold Christian workes. Reuerence
to the Word, hallowing the Sabaoths, releeuing
the poore, deeds of mercie, pittie, piety, giue a
delightful sent: solacing the soules of the Saints,
and pleasing him that made them both men and
