nor honour him dead. Good works are the best
ornaments, the most lasting monuments. They
become the house wherein thy soule dwelleth,
whiles it dwels there: and blesse thy memorie,
when those two are parted. A good life is mans
best monument: and that Epitaph shall last, as if
